hackathon-description-text: CornHacks aims to bring some of the most talented developers from around the Midwest to join in a weekend full of hacking.
hackathon-eligibility: Undergraduate students at UNL in teams of up to 4.

hackathon-judging-criteria.judging-criterion: How far they got in their project. Does it work? Did they execute it well?
Not how creative the idea itself is, but how they solved the problem. Their creativity in using tools to solve the problem at hand.
Does this have real-world implication? It could make a positive impact in anyway. Could be fun, time-saving, or any other helpful idea.
